Tutorial rails..

---------------------------------------------
Usando o email do gmail
----------------------------------------------

emails by gmail

script/plugin install http://code.openrain.com/rails/action_mailer_tls/

require "smtp_tls"

ActionMailer::Base.raise_delivery_errors = false
ActionMailer::Base.delivery_method = :smtp
ActionMailer::Base.server_settings = {
:address => "smtp.gmail.com",
:port => 587,
:domain => 'gmail.com',
:user_name => "convert.ruby.to@gmail.com",
:password => "rubyisred",
:authentication => :plain
}

---------------------------------------------
Instalando o Ruby + Ubuntu
----------------------------------------------

1° Passo

sudo apt-get install Ruby-full

Instalaçao do Ruby on rails no ubuntu
2° Passo
Instalando RubyGems

2.1) Download rubygems
wget http://rubyforge.org/frs/download.php/11289/rubygems-0.9.0.tgz

2.2) Descompactando
tar zxvf rubygems-0.9.0.tgz

2.3) Entrando no dir
cd rubygems-0.9.0

2.4) Instalando
sudo ruby setup.rb

2.5) Atualizando gem
gem update –system

3° Passo
Instalando Rails

sudo gem install rails –include-dependencies


---------------------------------------------
Erro usr/bin/gem:23: uninitialized constant Gem::GemRunner (NameError)
----------------------------------------------

adicionar essa linha em usr/bin/gem

require 'rubygems/gem_runner'

